## Pyro's HiDream Dev Workflow

### Models you need:

Put this in **'models/diffusion_models'**

[HiDream Dev](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/HiDream-I1_ComfyUI/blob/main/split_files/diffusion_models/hidream_i1_dev_bf16.safetensors)


Put these in **'models/text_encoders'**

#### [clip_l](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/HiDream-I1_ComfyUI/blob/main/split_files/text_encoders/clip_l_hidream.safetensors)

#### [clip_g](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/HiDream-I1_ComfyUI/blob/main/split_files/text_encoders/clip_g_hidream.safetensors)

#### [t5](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/HiDream-I1_ComfyUI/blob/main/split_files/text_encoders/t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors)

#### [llama 3.1](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/HiDream-I1_ComfyUI/blob/main/split_files/text_encoders/llama_3.1_8b_instruct_fp8_scaled.safetensors)

Put this into the **'models/vae'** folder

[ae](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/HiDream-I1_ComfyUI/blob/main/split_files/vae/ae.safetensors)

You can also use any Flux vae if you have any of them available

---------------------

If you have a potato GPU you can use City96's amazing GGUF quants (you need to replace the unet loader with City96's gguf unet loader)

[HiDream Dev GGUFs](https://huggingface.co/city96/HiDream-I1-Dev-gguf/tree/main)

Delete the **'Load HiDream Dev'** group and activate the **'Load HiDream Dev GGUF'** group instead

You can also use one of the NF4 loaders and get a NF4 quant, just replace the nodes correctly


---------------------

I highly recommend the custom node **'Detail Daemon Sampler'** which should be an easy install with ComfyUI Manager.

It adds more detail and makes the images sharper.

You probably only need to play around with the **'detail_amount'**

If you don't care and don't want to use custom nodes just delete the **'Detail Daemon Sampler'**
